[SN]TITLE[SN]
Nicholas Churchill's dumper truck rampage caught on camera

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have released footage showing a man on a 30-mile (48km) dumper truck rampage through Norfolk and Suffolk.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
5 February 2016 Last updated at 13:44 GMT
Nicholas Churchill, 40, of Brandon, Suffolk, stole the truck near Norwich and led police on chase down the A11 to Brandon, lasting two hours in July 2015.
He caused damage totalling Â£50,000, with two police cars being written-off and a third damaged.
Churchill was jailed for 14 months at Norwich Crown Court after admitting aggravated vehicle-taking and dangerous driving, and driving while unfit through drugs.
